[[Image:Okres lucenec.png|thumb|right|300px|Location of Lučenec District in the Banská Bystrica Region]] '''Gregorova Vieska''' ({{lang-hu|Gergelyfalva}}) is a village and municipality in the [[Lučenec District]] in the [[Banská Bystrica Region]] of [[Slovakia]]. [[Image:Slovakiakrajenumbers.png|left|thumb|300px|6: Banská Bystrica Region in Slovakia]]
==History== In [[history|historical records]], the [[village]] was first mentioned in 1393 (''Gergurfalua''). It belonged to [[Divín]] castle.
